HEADWORD: Gummous
<hw>Gum"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gummosus</ets>; cf. F. <ets>gommeux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Gumlike, or composed of gum; gummy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a
gumma.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gummy</ent>⟦br⟧
